gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Thunder 102, Timberwolves 97
gameRecap.excerpt: Led by Shai Gilgeous-Alexanders 33 points and six assists, the Thunder defeated the Timberwolves, 102-97. Gilgeous-Alexander notched his league-leading 30th 30+ point game of the season, while Chet Holmgren added 15 points, five rebounds and two blocks for the Thunder in the victory. Anthony Edwards tallied 19 points, five rebounds and five assists for the Timberwolves in the losing effort. The Thunder have won back-to-back games as they improve to 29-13 on the season, while the Timberwolves snap a 4-game winning streak as they fall to 30-12.
